N2  - An unmarried, 19 years old, Sudanese girl developed a firm right ovarian mass which increased in size to reach a diameter of 25 x 25 cm and a weight of 2.8 kg in 8 months time. The patient's condition was associated with amenorrhoea, polycystic ovary and ascites. The ovarian tumour was diagnosed by clinical examination and ultrasound scanning and was identified as a fibrothecoma by histopathology.
